headline: How Recent Developments Are Rewriting the Story for ConocoPhillips Stock
summary: ConocoPhillips’ latest price target was nudged slightly lower to about $112.37 as Wall Street analysts fine tuned their models for softer gas and NGL realizations within more conservative commodity assumptions. While several firms trimmed outer year growth expectations and cash flow forecasts, most continue to emphasize resilient production, healthy free cash flow potential, and disciplined capital returns as key supports for the long term story. Stay tuned to see how you can track these...
